MALAYSIA DAYBOOK: ECM Libra Shareholders Plot Exit, Star Bonds

-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-04-04T21:16:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/malaysia-daybook-ecm-libra-shareholders-plot-exit-star-bonds.html
ECM Libra Financial Group Bhd.’s
biggest shareholders have appointed an adviser to find a buyer
for the Malaysian securities firm and are considering three
proposals, a person with knowledge of the matter said.  Azman Hashim, ECM Libra’s biggest shareholder, Chairman
Kalimullah Hassan and Managing Director Lim Kian Onn are seeking
to either divest ECM Libra’s investment banking unit or sell the
entire company, said the person, who declined to be identified
as the talks are private. The three own a combined 34.9 percent
of ECM Libra’s shares, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Central bank Governor Zeti Akhtar Aziz to speak at Financial
Inclusion Policymakers Forum at 9 a.m. in  Kuala Lumpur .
* Prime Minister Najib Razak visits  South Korea .
* Star Publications (Malaysia) Bhd. (STAR MK) plans to sell as
much as 750 million ringgit of commercial papers to help fund
investments and capital expenditure. The company also plans to
sell another 750 million ringgit in medium-term notes.
* Aliran Ihsan Resources Bhd. (AIRB MK) won 28.3 million-ringgit
($9.4 million) contract from Pengurusan Aset Air Bhd. to upgrade
and rehabilitate an existing water plant in southern Johor state.
* Esso Malaysia Bhd. (ESSO MK) said it’s unaware of plans for
Boustead Holdings Bhd. (BOUS MK) and its parent to acquire a
stake.
* YTL Cement Bhd. (YTLC MK) scrapped a $200 million exchangeable
bond sale.  MARKETS:
*  Malaysia ’s FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI Index was little changed.
* The MSCI Asia Pacific Index increased 0.5 percent.
* The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  gained 0.2 percent.
* Palm oil June-delivery futures advanced 1.3 percent to 3,382
ringgit a metric ton.  BTV HIGHLIGHTS (KL time):
*7:10am SY University of Sydney Prof Brendan Kennedy
*7:40am HK ‘IPO: A Global Guide’ Author Philippe Espinasse
*9:10am CB Univ of NSW Nuclear Physicist Dr. Heiko Timmers
*9:20am WE NZ FinMin/Deputy PM Bill English
